#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 3. Dutiyasotāpannasutta → dutiyasotasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn48.3:0.3"
msgid "3. Dutiyasotāpannasutta "
msgstr "3. A Stream-Enterer (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.194, sc1
msgctxt "sn48.3:1.1"
msgid "“Pañcimāni, bhikkhave, indriyāni. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five faculties. "

msgctxt "sn48.3:1.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn48.3:1.3"
msgid "Saddhindriyaṃ, vīriyindriyaṃ, satindriyaṃ, samādhindriyaṃ, paññindriyaṃ. "
msgstr "The faculties of faith, energy, mindfulness, immersion, and wisdom. "

msgctxt "sn48.3:1.4"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako imesaṃ pañcannaṃ indriyānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti—"
msgstr "A noble disciple comes to truly understand these five faculties’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape. "

msgctxt "sn48.3:1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyaṇo”ti. "
msgstr "Such a noble disciple is called a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.3:1.6"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ. "
msgstr ""

